Strings : this a non primitive data type. strings are used for storing and processing text

// string declaration

String name = "karuna K";


String name = new String();
name = "karuna K";

note : String is a class in java.



// to find length of string
String name = "karuna K";

name.length(); //8

// to convert a string to upper case

.toUpperCase();

name.toUpperCase();  // KARUNA K


// to convert a string to lower case

.toLowerCase();

name.toLowerCase();  // karuna k

